projectInfo.name: Missing Maps: Buildings in South Kivu, DRC (5)
projectInfo.shortDescription: In South Kivu, a province in the east of the Democratic Republic of Congo there are many factors favouring the spread of diseases such as armed conflict and a displaced population. MSF teams working here respond to a variety of different health needs. These include interventions in communities with community health agents to support primary health centres. Accurate maps of the area will assist the teams in their work, especially in areas that are difficult to access either for geographical and/or security reasons.

projectInfo.instructions:
Imagery 
========================
Please use Maxar Premium Imagery. The imagery will load automatically when you open a task. 

Buildings
=========================
Please **map all** buildings.

Buildings are generally squared and round huts with straw or tin roofs. They are sometimes **not easy to spot**, so please scan the area very carefully.  But be aware, don't confuse them with trees and rocks!

**For rectangular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an area and label it as **Building**, then correct for right angles with the **Q** key.
* In JOSM: draw an area and use the tag **building=yes**, then correct for right angles using the **Q** key - OR use the building plugin.

**For circular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw a triangular area over the building and use the tag **Building**, then correct to make the shape circular with the **O** key.
* In JOSM: draw a line on the diameter of the building and use the tag **building=yes**, then hit **Shift+O** to make the shape circular - OR use the building plugin. 

Roads and other features
========================
Your are not requested to map anything other than buildings in this project. In iD there is set a project restriction to map only buildings, but in JOSM you are able to map more features. It is not requested in this task, but if you choose to do so, please check the [Highway Africa Tag page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Highway_Tag_Africa) for advice on tagging roads and see [the OSM map features page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Map_Features) for more information on general OSM tagging.

Bonjour @[Joss2Lyon],
La cartographie est très bien réalisée ! Voici quelques suggestions pour t'améliorer.
-Guetter les ombres : un carré clair sans ombre alors que tous les autres en ont, ce n'est pas un bâtiment. Cela peut être une zone défrichée, un stade de foot...
-Une ombre interne, en forme de rectangle, c'est généralement un bâtiment en construction. Donc soit on ne le met pas, soit on le met en building=construction.
-Bien regarder toute la zone. Ici il y avait des zones au sud oubliées (avec leurs pauvres petits bâtiments abandonnées). Donc balayer Nord/sud ou est/ouest.

N'hésite pas à t'aider de l'ombre pour trouver les bâtiments. Un carré avec une ombre, et en plus s'il y a une route dans les environs c'est la jackpot !
